<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SummitShips     11-26 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Summit Ships,0096</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Navy Ship Arrives for Superpower Summit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VALLETTA, Malta (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The USS Belknap, the American naval ship
to be used for the superpower summit, arrived in Maltese waters
Sunday. Maltese officials said the Soviet crusier Slava is expected
Tuesday or Wednesday.
   Malta gave the summit ships diplomatic clearance after both the
United States and the Soviet Union conformed with a Maltese
Parliament resolution prohibiting ships carrying nuclear armaments
from entering Maltese territory.
   President Bush and Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev are to
meet Dec. 2 and Dec. 3 on the ships.
</TEXT>
