<HEAD>Airport Exec's Car Damaged in Airport Garage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KENNER, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Even the chairman of the New Orleans Aviation
Board is joining the list of people unhappy about the new parking
garage at New Orleans International Airport.
   Stephen Murray returned home from a vacation to discover that a
leak in the garage ceiling directly over his reserved parking spot
had damaged the paint on his wife's new Mercedes Benz convertible.
   ``I'm not too upset, as long as the people responsible for the
claim repair my car,'' he said. ``In the meantime, I told them to
find me another parking spot.''
   Airport patrons say the garage, which ran millions of dollars
over budget, is difficult to maneuver in, the traffic flow is
confusing and there aren't enough signs. Architects consulted by
The Times-Picayune said it cost nearly twice as much per space as
did four other major parking garages completed in the area over the
past seven years.
