<FIRST>r a AM-Obit-Murphy     11-26 0209</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Murphy,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>William C. Murphy, Vice President Quayle's Uncle, Dies At 67</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   William C. Murphy, an uncle of Vice President
Dan Quayle and a former executive of Eli Lilly and Co., has died at
the age of 67.
   Murphy, married to a sister of Quayle's mother, died Wednesday.
He had been hospitalized with a heart ailment.
   Quayle press secretary Dave Beckwith said Sunday that the vice
president would attend a memorial service Monday at the Fourth
Presbyterian Church in Bethesda, Md., but did not think he would go
to the burial at Franklin, Ind.
   Quayle had been scheduled to address the National League of
Cities meeting Monday in Atlanta, but cancelled that because of his
uncle's death.
   Murphy was manager of Lilly's public information department in
Indianapolis before going to Washington, where he directed Lilly's
public relations office from 1964 until he retired in 1975.
   He received a Brookings Institute Fellowship in Washington in
January 1964.
   After his retirement, he continued to work for the
Indianapolis-based pharmaceutical company through his own firm,
Murphy and Associates.
   During World War II, Murphy piloted 33 missions over Europe in
B-17 bombers.
   Survivors include his wife, Suzanne Pulliam Murphy, whose sister
Corinne Pulliam Quayle is the vice president's mother.
</TEXT>
