<HEAD>Two Fighter Planes Collide, Four Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Philippine air force planes
collided Monday and crashed into a rice paddy near this southern
city, killing all four crewmen, a military spokesman said.
   The T-28 single-engine planes were approaching the runway here
when they collided at an altitude of about 3,300 feet, said Maj.
Dave Reyes, spokesman for the air force 3rd division.
   He said a third T-28 in the formation landed safely.
   The three planes were flying to Zamboanga from Cotabato City,
150 miles east of Zamboanga, according to Reyes. He said the cause
of the accident has not been determined.
</TEXT>
